        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         This pipe dream some of you guys are living is rather humerous. I don't want any more buffing power. Necromancers IMO, are not meant to be buffers. We are meant to control undead and kill shit flat out. I mean think about it, out of all the DnD games youhave played or all the books you have read what was a Necros role? They had a bg old undead army or a pet undead dragon and they just liked making shit decay.</P><P>Where we need to be looked at is on the raid level. Pet resists to dynamically match ours was a big step in the right direction. What we need now is some way to stack dots. Groups love us now because of the 1k group heal we have and a group mana tap plus a nasty spec pet that stuns. did I mention the 35+ attk that we can give the tanks in our group, oh and don't forget our undead slow.</P><P><BR>Gimme a Curse spell that makes dragons and snakes cry and I will be a happy camper.</P><P></P><P>Phyrexian Fleshreaver<BR>60 Warlock<BR>Quellious<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
